# Components Guide

The project uses a component-based architecture with the following structure:

## Main Components
- [app-header.tsx](mdc:src/components/app-header.tsx) - Main application header
- [coach-loop-logo.tsx](mdc:src/components/coach-loop-logo.tsx) - Logo component
- [insights-display-card.tsx](mdc:src/components/insights-display-card.tsx) - Card for displaying insights
- [transcript-form.tsx](mdc:src/components/transcript-form.tsx) - Form for handling transcripts
- [action-item-card.tsx](mdc:src/components/action-item-card.tsx) - Card for displaying action items

## UI Components
The `ui/` directory contains reusable UI components that follow a consistent design system. These components are built using Tailwind CSS and should be used for maintaining design consistency across the application.

When creating new components:
1. Place reusable UI components in the `ui/` directory
2. Place page-specific components in the `src/components` directory
3. Follow the existing naming convention: `component-name.tsx`
4. Use TypeScript for type safety
5. Implement proper prop types and documentation
